@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About";
}

<!-- PAGE HEADING -->
<div class="my-4 steam-background-wrapper p-steam-bgwrapper">
    <div class="col-12 col-lg-8">
        <h1 class="steam-white-text"><span class="steam-grey-text">About</span> this project</h1>
        <div class="black-box"></div>
        <hr class="w-100" />

        <div class="my-4">
            <p class="steam-grey-text">
                GameStore is a passion project born from a love of retro web design and nostalgia. 
                The goal was to create a functional game library management system while paying homage to the iconic Steam client interface from the early 2000s. 
                This project demonstrates how effective a well-designed, minimalist UI can be, even decades later.
            </p>
            <p class="steam-grey-text">
                The design is heavily inspired by the original Steam website and client from 2002-2005. 
                During that era, Steam was revolutionary—a simple, no-nonsense platform for purchasing and managing games. 
                The green-on-dark color scheme, bold typography, and straightforward layouts defined that era of digital design. 
                This project captures that aesthetic while building a modern, fully functional application.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="my-4">
            <h5 class="steam-light-green-text">Features</h5>
            <p class="steam-grey-text">
                Built with .NET 9 and ASP.NET Core Razor Pages, GameStore leverages modern technologies while maintaining a retro presentation layer. 
                The backend integrates with the IGDB (Internet Game Database) API to fetch real game data, including cover art, descriptions, genres, 
                and platform information. Entity Framework Core handles data persistence with SQL Server, and ASP.NET Identity provides secure authentication.
            </p>
            <ul class="steam-grey-text">
                <li><strong>Admin Dashboard:</strong> Create, edit, and delete games with full CRUD operations.</li>
                <li><strong>IGDB Integration:</strong> Search for games by name and automatically populate metadata.</li>
                <li><strong>Game Library:</strong> Browse and view detailed information about every game in the store.</li>
                <li><strong>User Authentication:</strong> Secure login and registration with role-based access control.</li>
                <li><strong>Responsive Design:</strong> Works seamlessly across desktop, tablet, and mobile devices.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>


        <div class="my-4">
            <h5 class="steam-light-green-text">Why Retro Design?</h5>
            <p class="steam-grey-text">
                Retro design isn't just nostalgia—it's about clarity and purpose. The Steam aesthetic from that era proves that simplicity, 
                good color contrast, and logical layout create an intuitive user experience. By building with this style, we challenge the notion 
                that modern = complex, and show that purposeful, clean design transcends trends.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
